# Vibe Basic Guardrails

## Timing Rules
- Do not change fixed timing constants (`ROULETTE_STOP_COMP_MS`, `ROULETTE_ANGLE_COMP_DEG`) without explicit user approval.
- Use only `sent_unix_ms`-based dynamic lag compensation for timing alignment.
- Do not change `NETWORK_LAG_COMP_MAX_MS` without timing-debug evidence.

## Work Rules
- Fix one issue at a time; no multi-fix commits.
- Separate stability fixes from refactor/style changes.
- Keep rollback-safe commits small and clear.

## Verification Rules
- For timing-related changes, verify on both Chrome and Whale.
- Run at least 3 rounds and check timing-debug logs before concluding.
